attributes.Long form description: The student approaches the table to start to assemble it. He has problems adjusting the correct position for the base of the table. But after shifting the legs, he unites them. The student screws the two hex socket heads that clasp the base together. Once the circle is placed, the student screws the two hex socket heads that hold the circle. To finish, the student places the tray on the base.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should turn the other leg

attributes.Transcription: You should turn the one that you're holding in your right hand, of course, so the top should be done and the downer part should be up.
